      <Meanings>
        <Meaning id="06d8aa27-de17-4a66-b9d7-de683b0c7631" type="Noun">
          <Vi>Vật liệu bán dẫn</Vi>
          <En>A solid material that has electrical conductivity between that of a conductor and an insulator, and whose conductivity can be controlled by adding impurities or applying electric fields.</En>
          <Example>The silicon wafer used in computer chips is a semiconductor.</Example>
          <IsArchaic>false</IsArchaic>
          <Situations>
            <Situation id="e04a2351-73b5-46b1-8cdd-bd9b223e2938">
              <Vi>Mô tả vật liệu có tính dẫn điện điều chỉnh được, dùng trong linh kiện điện tử.</Vi>
              <En>Describes a material with controllable electrical conductivity, used in electronic components.</En>
            </Situation>
            <Situation id="e3f71192-199a-43c4-998c-879738881df0">
              <Vi>Kỹ thuật chế tạo chip vi xử lý và đèn LED.</Vi>
              <En>Technology involved in manufacturing microprocessors and LEDs.</En>
